# Docker Port Mapping Notes

## What I learned

Docker port mapping is used to access conatiners from browser.
Example:

docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx

8080 = local machine port  
80 = conatiner port
After running this command:
http://localhost:8080

opens nginx webpage.

## Learnings

- Learned basic port mapping
- Understood how browser connects to conatiner
- Docker helps in app deploument
- Containers isolate applications
